On my quest (really?) I encountered three pups who were really uncomfortable of me being around and clicking them. They would run away every time I came closer to them. 😅
But then my mom opened up a cashew packet we had got earlier which got them all cheered up. 🐕
They really got excited to know what was in the packet and came to me with those puppy eyes. 🐶
Dissappointed they went back knowing they were cashews. I guess they didn't liked it. 😶
One of them crawled back to his home under the car. I followed him and slowly tried to get as close as I could for a click. 🙇🏻‍♂️
I was surprised this time to find out he was little comfortable with me clicking him this time. 😭
Thats how I got this one, where he is directly looking in the camera. 💁🏻‍♂️
.
.
.

There was a kite festival arranged in college ground by slum boys, nobody knew, unless boys running after the kites which got cut were seen...Then I met this little guy with this big bamboo, maybe to reach to the kites stuck somewhere high. He had four kites,Each of different colors. When I asked them about kites he just said "Don't touch them" as if it was his priced possession. He didn't talk with me much as he was busy keeping an eye on kites.... I thought I had met such kid before, maybe he was just like Hassan from the book Kite Runner. Yes I met a kite runner today!

caption.text:
This time in Goa I didn't wanted to visit those mainstream beaches, I decided to go to those churches all Tourism agencies advertised about. But didn't booked a tour,they give a limited time to visit these monuments.

Boarding a bus was a better option and got there by myself... So I started with Bom Jesus church,where thousands of people visit everyday,many tourists and some local. Then visiting two more churches and having my lunch,exploring that tall structure on top of the hill is all I wanted! Asking for the directions I got to know it is remnants of an old church. Walking half kilometer up the hill,exhausted and my phone about to die I got here.

A lush green garden welcomed me and behind it this tower standing tall, broken but not bent! Only one of the four towers remains and still it shines in its glory...How beautiful it must be back then?
